example_sequence:
When asked to send a message on WhatsApp, you MUST generate this exact sequence:
1. {"action": "open_app", "name": "WhatsApp"}
2. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "ctrl+f"}
3. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<Contact Name>"}
4. {"action": "wait_until", "condition": "search results load"}
5. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "tab"}
6. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "enter"}
7. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<The Message>"}
8. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "enter"}

When asked to play a video on YouTube, generate this sequence:
1. {"action": "open_browser", "url": "https://youtube.com"}
2. {"action": "wait_until", "condition": "YouTube homepage loads"}
3. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "/"} (to focus search bar)
4. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<Video Name>"}
5. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "enter"}
6. {"action": "wait_until", "condition": "search results appear"}
7. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "tab"} (multiple times if needed to reach first video)
8. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "enter"}

When asked to send an email via Gmail, generate this sequence:
1. {"action": "open_browser", "url": "https://mail.google.com"}
2. {"action": "wait_until", "condition": "Gmail loads"}
3. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "c"} (Gmail shortcut to compose)
4. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<Recipient Email>"}
5. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "enter"}
6. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "tab"}
7. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<Subject Line>"}
8. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "tab"}
9. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<Email Body>"}
10. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "ctrl+enter"} (Gmail shortcut to send)

When asked to search the web or look something up on Google, generate this sequence:
1. {"action": "open_browser", "url": "https://google.com"}
2. {"action": "wait_until", "condition": "Google search bar is focused"}
3. {"action": "type_text", "text": "<Search Query>"}
4. {"action": "key_shortcut", "keys": "enter"}
5. {"action": "wait_until", "condition": "search results page loads"}
